   <div class = "entry">
      <div class="entrybody" id="https://www.accessnow.org/blog/2014/07/22/civil-society-groups-alert-european-commission-to-uks-breach-of-eu-law#When:13:28:47Z">

         <div class="entrytitle" >
            <div class="entrytitleauthor"><a href="https://www.accessnow.org/blog/rss/" title="Access Blog">Access </a></div><br />
         

            <a href="https://www.accessnow.org/blog/2014/07/22/civil-society-groups-alert-european-commission-to-uks-breach-of-eu-law">Civil society groups alert European Commission to UK’s breach of EU Law</a> 
        </div>

         <div class="content">
            <p>Today Access, together with 20 digital and civil rights organisations, sent the following letter (linked here and below) to E.U. Commissioners Michel Barnier and Cecilia Malmstr&#246;m to bring their attention to an infringement of E.U. law by the United Kingdom through the adoption of the Data Retention and Investigatory Powers Act (&#8220;DRIP&#8221;).</p>
          </div>
                        
         <p align="right">
            <a href="https://www.accessnow.org/blog/2014/07/22/civil-society-groups-alert-european-commission-to-uks-breach-of-eu-law">
            Access | Access Blog | 
            2014-07-22 13:28:47</a></a>
         </p>
