        </div>

         <div class="content">
            <p>This week the U.K. Parliament adopted the &#8220;Data Retention and Investigatory Powers Act,&#8221; or DRIP, a bill that would dramatically expand the government&#8217;s surveillance powers. In the runup to the vote, the GCHQ, civil service, and coalition and opposition leaders showed a flagrant disregard for parliamentary procedure and failed to allow an informed and public debate. The result is a terrible bill that would treat all citizens, in the U.K. and abroad, as surveillance targets.</p>
          </div>
                        
         <p align="right">
